<subSubSection id="0FC96579FFED89697DCDA36AB892FF57" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="description">
<paragraph id="476C36F2FFED89697DCDA36ABB3DFF0D" blockId="59.[151,1436,296,1792]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697DCDA36ABB7CFD5E" bold="true" box="[199,351,335,361]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Description.</emphasis>
Medium to large leafhoppers. Crown flattened and spatulate, anterior margin foliaceous; ocelli on crown, closer to each other than to eyes, texture coarsely rugose or deeply punctate; face convex; frontoclypeus expanded and convex, visible in lateral view, with numerous punctuations; antennal pits weakly defined or absent, inner margins sometimes a thin carina adjacent to frontoclypeus; antennal ledges absent or present, if present, then as a thin anterior carina projecting forward only slightly and merging with the marginal carina of the crown; pronotum broad and usually distinctly elevated, often with distinct ridges, texture coarsely rugose or deeply punctate; forewing venation simple with cells well defined, appendix absent or present, but if present, generally broad and reaching completely around apex of wing; proepisternum exposed, large, long and narrow, or small and tab-like; metathoracic femur apical macrosetal formula 2+1; metathoracic tibia rows I and II with large macrosetae. Male genitalia: pygofer with or without apical setal patch; aedeagus often with laterally compressed and more-or-less triangular dorsomedial lobe, long and slender apically, often curving dorsad. Female genitalia: valvulae II long and very slender, moderately sclerotized.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="476C36F2FFED89697DCDA163B892FF57" blockId="59.[151,1436,296,1792]" box="[199,689,838,864]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697DCDA163BB3DFF57" bold="true" box="[199,286,838,864]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Range.</emphasis>
Nearctic and Neotropical regions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0FC96579FFED89697DCDA148BB6CF815" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="476C36F2FFED89697DCDA148BB6CF815" blockId="59.[151,1436,296,1792]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697DCDA148BB13FFB0" bold="true" box="[199,304,877,903]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Ecology.</emphasis>
Generally associated with grasses, although the first author has collected 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED896979B2A148BF06FFB1" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1850" box="[1208,1317,877,902]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Proranus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED896979B2A148BF06FFB1" box="[1208,1317,877,902]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Proranus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in mixed forbs on steep, tree-covered hillsides, above streams in south-central 
<collectingCountry id="3FC47662FFED89697EDDA1B1BE79FF99" box="[983,1114,916,942]" name="Guatemala" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="23424B03FFED8969796DA1B1BF3FFF99" author="Lawson, P. B." box="[1127,1308,916,942]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" pagination="159 - 169" refId="ref57977" refString="Lawson, P. B. (1931) The genus Xerophloea in North America (Homoptera, Cicadellidae). Pan-Pacific Entomology, 7, 159 - 169." type="journal article" year="1931">Lawson (1931)</bibRefCitation>
noted that members of 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697C26A19FBB97FFE4" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1803" box="[300,436,954,979]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xerophloea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697C26A19FBB97FFE4" box="[300,436,954,979]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Xerophloea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are occasionally abundant in an area, and 
<bibRefCitation id="23424B03FFED89697EBAA19FBE6DFFE3" author="Oman, P. W." box="[944,1102,954,980]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" pagination="1 - 253" refId="ref59042" refString="Oman, P. W. (1949) The Nearctic leafhoppers (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). A generic classification and check list. Memoirs of the Entomological Society of Washington, 3, 1 - 253." type="journal article" year="1949">
<collectingCountry id="3FC47662FFED89697EBAA19FB9DBFFE3" box="[944,1016,954,980]" name="Oman" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Oman</collectingCountry>
(1949)
</bibRefCitation>
suggested that during those times, 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697DEEA1C4BB4FFFCD" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1803" box="[228,364,993,1018]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xerophloea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697DEEA1C4BB4FFFCD" box="[228,364,993,1018]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Xerophloea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might constitute a forage pest. Some species of 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697EAAA1C4BE0BFFCD" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1803" box="[928,1064,993,1018]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xerophloea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697EAAA1C4BE0BFFCD" box="[928,1064,993,1018]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Xerophloea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be vectors of plant disease (
<bibRefCitation id="23424B03FFED89697D95A62DBB61F815" author="Nielson, M. W." box="[159,322,1032,1058]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" pagination="234 - 244" refId="ref58885" refString="Nielson, M. W. (1962) A revision of the genus Xerophloea (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 55, 234 - 244." type="journal article" year="1962">Nielson 1962</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0FC96579FFED89697DCDA60BBE15FB37" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="476C36F2FFED89697DCDA60BB9C3F992" blockId="59.[151,1436,296,1792]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697DCDA60BBB63F87F" bold="true" box="[199,320,1070,1096]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697C42A60AB811F87F" authority="Germar" authorityName="Germar" authorityYear="1839" box="[328,562,1070,1096]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xerophloea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697C42A60ABBF3F87F" box="[328,464,1071,1096]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Xerophloea</emphasis>
Germar
</taxonomicName>
was placed in its own subfamily by 
<collectingCountry id="3FC47662FFED89697EEDA60BBE0CF87F" box="[999,1071,1070,1096]" name="Oman" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Oman</collectingCountry>
(1943), and 
<bibRefCitation id="23424B03FFED896979C2A60BBF46F87F" author="Evans, J. W." box="[1224,1381,1070,1096]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" pagination="105 - 271" refId="ref56200" refString="Evans, J. W. (1947) A natural classification of the leaf-hoppers (Jassoidea, Homoptera). Part 3: Jassidae. Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 98, 105 - 271." type="journal article" year="1947">Evans (1947)</bibRefCitation>
was the first to include it in 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697CCAA670B80FF858" authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1855" box="[448,556,1109,1135]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ledrinae">Ledrinae</taxonomicName>
. Later (1949), 
<collectingCountry id="3FC47662FFED89697FEFA670B90FF858" box="[741,812,1109,1135]" name="Oman" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Oman</collectingCountry>
elevated it to tribal level within 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED896979CFA670BF12F858" authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1855" box="[1221,1329,1109,1135]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ledrinae">Ledrinae</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="23424B03FFED89697835A670BAC6F8A1" author="Szwedo, J." pageId="59" pageNumber="60" pagination="153 - 163" refId="ref59765" refString="Szwedo, J. (2002) Studies on Xerophloeini leafhoppers with description of Pariacaca icanoensis gen. and sp. nov. from Argentina (Hemiptera: Cicadomorpha: Cicadellidae: Ledrinae). Genus, 13, 153 - 163." type="journal article" year="2002">Szwedo (2002)</bibRefCitation>
considered this tribe to include a number of genera, namely 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697EF0A659BE44F8A2" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1850" box="[1018,1127,1148,1173]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Proranus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697EF0A659BE44F8A2" box="[1018,1127,1148,1173]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Proranus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697977A659BF26F8A2" authorityName="Germar" authorityYear="1839" box="[1149,1285,1148,1173]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xerophloea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697977A659BF26F8A2" box="[1149,1285,1148,1173]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Xerophloea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697811A659BFB6F8A2" authorityName="Szwedo" authorityYear="2002" box="[1307,1429,1148,1173]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pariacaca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697811A659BFB6F8A2" box="[1307,1429,1148,1173]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Pariacaca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697D9DA686BB07F88B" authorityName="Kramer" authorityYear="1966" box="[151,292,1187,1212]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hespenedra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697D9DA686BB07F88B" box="[151,292,1187,1212]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Hespenedra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697C3EA686BBBDF88B" authorityName="Kramer" authorityYear="1966" box="[308,414,1187,1212]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xedreota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697C3EA686BBBDF88B" box="[308,414,1187,1212]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Xedreota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and possibly 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697F43A686B8E6F88B" authorityName="Osborn" authorityYear="1938" box="[585,709,1187,1212]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Clinonana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697F43A686B8E6F88B" box="[585,709,1187,1212]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Clinonana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but he gave no characters uniting the group. In this analysis, 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697D9DA6ECBB06F8D5" authorityName="Kramer" authorityYear="1966" box="[151,293,1225,1250]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hespenedra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697D9DA6ECBB06F8D5" box="[151,293,1225,1250]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Hespenedra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697C6BA6ECBBFEF8D5" authorityName="Osborn" authorityYear="1938" box="[353,477,1225,1250]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Clinonana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697C6BA6ECBBFEF8D5" box="[353,477,1225,1250]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Clinonana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are shown to not belong within 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697E6FA6ECBE20F8D4" authorityName="Oman" authorityYear="1949" box="[869,1027,1225,1251]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Xerophloeini">Xerophloeini</taxonomicName>
, while 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697951A6ECBEEBF8D5" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1850" box="[1115,1224,1225,1250]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Proranus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697951A6ECBEEBF8D5" box="[1115,1224,1225,1250]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Proranus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED896979D3A6ECBF42F8D5" authorityName="Germar" authorityYear="1839" box="[1241,1377,1225,1250]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xerophloea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED896979D3A6ECBF42F8D5" box="[1241,1377,1225,1250]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Xerophloea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697D9DA6D5BB22F93E" authorityName="Kramer" authorityYear="1966" box="[151,257,1264,1289]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xedreota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697D9DA6D5BB22F93E" box="[151,257,1264,1289]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Xedreota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
do. 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697C35A6D5BB9AF93E" authorityName="Szwedo" authorityYear="2002" box="[319,441,1264,1289]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pariacaca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697C35A6D5BB9AF93E" box="[319,441,1264,1289]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Pariacaca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, though not examined, appears from Szwedo’s drawings and description to also belong in 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697C07A733BB88F907" authorityName="Oman" authorityYear="1949" box="[269,427,1302,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Xerophloeini">Xerophloeini</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697CBCA732B8D9F907" authority="Spinola 1850" authorityName="Spinola. He" authorityYear="1850" box="[438,762,1302,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Piezauchenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697CBCA732B877F907" box="[438,596,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Piezauchenia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="23424B03FFED89697F56A733B8D9F907" author="Spinola, M." box="[604,762,1302,1328]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" pagination="61 - 138" refId="ref59469" refString="Spinola, M. (1850) Di alcuni generi d'insetti artroidignati nuovamente proposti dal socio attuale Signor Marchese Massimiliano Spinola nella sua tavola sinottica di questo ordine che precede la presente memoria. Modena Memorie di Matematica e Fisica della Societa Italiana delle Scienze, residente in Modena, 25, 61 - 138." type="journal article" year="1850">Spinola 1850</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, included in 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697E99A733BE0EF907" authorityName="Oman" authorityYear="1949" box="[915,1069,1302,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Xerophloeini">Xerophloeini</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="23424B03FFED89697950A733BF16F907" author="Linnavuori, R." box="[1114,1333,1302,1328]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" pagination="1 - 370" refId="ref58114" refString="Linnavuori, R. (1959) Revision of the Neotropical Deltocephalinae and some related subfamilies (Homoptera). Suomalaisen Elain - ja Kasvitieteellisen Seuran Vanamon Elaintieteellisia Julkaisuja, 20, 1 - 370." type="journal article" year="1959">Linnavuori (1959)</bibRefCitation>
, was not available for examination, and its placement is here considered 
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697E76A718BE3DF961" box="[892,1054,1341,1366]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">incertae sedis</emphasis>
within 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED8969797DA718BF2EF960" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1825" box="[1143,1293,1341,1367]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cicadellidae</taxonomicName>
. The extinct genus 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697DEEA741BBABF94A" authorityName="Hamilton" authorityYear="1990" box="[228,392,1380,1405]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paracarsonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697DEEA741BBABF94A" box="[228,392,1380,1405]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Paracarsonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, treated above in &quot;Biogeographic considerations and fossil evidence&quot; under Results and Discussion section, is also herein recognized to belong to 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697E37A7AEB9F8F992" authorityName="Oman" authorityYear="1949" box="[829,987,1419,1445]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Xerophloeini">Xerophloeini</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="476C36F2FFED89697DCCA794BF2CFA84" blockId="59.[151,1436,296,1792]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
Though distinct in many ways, 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697F3EA794B8EDF9FC" authorityName="Oman" authorityYear="1949" box="[564,718,1457,1483]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Xerophloeini">Xerophloeini</taxonomicName>
share many features with other 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697948A794BE89F9FC" authorityName="Fairmaire" authorityYear="1855" box="[1090,1194,1457,1483]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ledrinae">Ledrinae</taxonomicName>
and especially some herein newly recognized members of 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697F6DA7FDB8D1F9C5" authorityName="Jones" authorityYear="2009" box="[615,754,1496,1522]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Afrorubrini">Afrorubrini</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697E08A7FDB94FF9C6" authorityName="Kramer" authorityYear="1966" box="[770,876,1496,1521]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xedreota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697E08A7FDB94FF9C6" box="[770,876,1496,1521]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Xedreota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and “Genus 4” have distinct similarities (see discussion for 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697C52A7DABBE1FA2F" authorityName="Kramer" authorityYear="1966" box="[344,450,1535,1560]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xedreota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697C52A7DABBE1FA2F" box="[344,450,1535,1560]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Xedreota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), as do 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697F4BA7DAB8EAFA2F" authorityName="Germar" authorityYear="1839" box="[577,713,1535,1560]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xerophloea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697F4BA7DAB8EAFA2F" box="[577,713,1535,1560]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Xerophloea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and one undescribed afrorubrine genus (“Genus 3” in phylogenetic analysis). In general, 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697F38A400B89AFA08" authorityName="Jones" authorityYear="2009" box="[562,697,1573,1599]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Afrorubrini">Afrorubrini</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697FF8A400B9AEFA08" authorityName="Oman" authorityYear="1949" box="[754,909,1573,1599]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Xerophloeini">Xerophloeini</taxonomicName>
share valvulae II being long and slender and intermediately sclerotized, with two dorsal teeth and other supernumerary teeth. 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED896979AEA469BF31FA52" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1850" box="[1188,1298,1612,1637]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Proranus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED896979AEA469BF31FA52" box="[1188,1298,1612,1637]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Proranus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697820A469BFB7FA52" authorityName="Kramer" authorityYear="1966" box="[1322,1428,1612,1637]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xedreota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697820A469BFB7FA52" box="[1322,1428,1612,1637]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Xedreota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697D9DA456BB3CFABB" authorityName="Germar" authorityYear="1839" box="[151,287,1651,1676]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xerophloea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697D9DA456BB3CFABB" box="[151,287,1651,1676]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Xerophloea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, Genus 2, Genus 3, and Genus 4 all share punctuations on the frontoclypeus, and the frontoclypeus being expanded and convex with the anterior foliaceous portion of the crown short.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="476C36F2FFED89697DCCA4E5BE15FB37" blockId="59.[151,1436,296,1792]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
The following genera are herein included in 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697E14A4E5B99EFAED" authorityName="Oman" authorityYear="1949" box="[798,957,1728,1754]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Xerophloeini">Xerophloeini</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697EDEA4E5BE5BFAEE" authorityName="Hamilton" authorityYear="1990" box="[980,1144,1728,1753]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paracarsonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697EDEA4E5BE5BFAEE" box="[980,1144,1728,1753]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Paracarsonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697998A4E5BFB6FAEE" box="[1170,1429,1728,1753]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697998A4E5BF2CFAEE" authorityName="Szwedo" authorityYear="2002" box="[1170,1295,1728,1753]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pariacaca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pariacaca</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED8969782CA4E5BFB6FAEE" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1850" box="[1318,1429,1728,1753]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Proranus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Proranus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697D9DA4C2BB21FB37" authorityName="Kramer" authorityYear="1966" box="[151,258,1767,1792]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xedreota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697D9DA4C2BB21FB37" box="[151,258,1767,1792]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Xedreota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697C49A4C2BBE8FB37" authorityName="Germar" authorityYear="1839" box="[323,459,1767,1792]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xerophloea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697C49A4C2BBE8FB37" box="[323,459,1767,1792]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Xerophloea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The extinct genus 
<taxonomicName id="80D34D71FFED89697FBBA4C2B976FB37" authorityName="Hamilton" authorityYear="1990" box="[689,853,1767,1792]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paracarsonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="75A7EAE0FFED89697FBBA4C2B976FB37" box="[689,853,1767,1792]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Paracarsonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not treated here.
</paragraph>
